title: United Kingdom House of Commons Speeches Collection
description: LibriVox United Kingdom House of Commons speeches collection. This collection comprises recordings of 17 historic speeches given to the UK House of Commons between 1628 and 1956. Readings are of speeches origninally given by parliamentarians including Oliver Cromwell, Edmund Burke, William Wilberforce, William Gladstone, Keir Hardie, Winston Churchill and Aneurin Bevan. (Summary by Carl Manchester) M4B format available
subject: politics; parliament; audiobook; librivox; labour; conservative; liberal
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
